description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic and motivated Registered Nurse committed to delivering excellent patient care to join our community nursing team based at Yate Westgate Centre.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Community Nursing service plan and deliver evidence based nursing care to housebound patients within defined localities. You will work both autonomously and collaboratively within supportive teams which comprise of Community Nurse Team Leaders , Community Nurses, Healthcare Assistants and Administrators as well as with the wider healthcare community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need excellent communication and clinical skills and have experience of working within a team; previous community experience is desirable but not essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will also be required to use electronic patient record systems, have good time management and be able to prioritise your work load effectively.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Weekend and bank holiday working and some late shifts will be part of this role. You need to have access to a car with a full driving license to apply&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information about this role, please contact Hazel Roddan District Nurse Team Leader on 07979754574&lt;/p&gt;
